I had this error in my output_log after it loaded my landing legs and wheels:

WheelCollider requires an attached Rigidbody to function.

Also had this error:

Cannot find a Module of typename 'KASModuleGrab'

But it's on the correct location. It worked before and now it doesn't.

Edited July 16, 2014 by Olympic1

I had this error in my output_log after it loaded my landing legs and wheels:

WheelCollider requires an attached Rigidbody to function.

This is an issue with the stock wheels (or some of them). I get this error about 4 times every time I switch to flight mode. 99.9% of the time it can be ignored and even if you are using one of the wheels in question it might cause an odd ride as the wheel is not quite where the game thinks it is.

Also had this error:

Cannot find a Module of typename 'KASModuleGrab'

But it's on the correct location. It worked before and now it doesn't.

KAS is the Kerbal Attachement System. All that error means is something has gone wrong. As I don't use KAS myself I can't tell you anything more about this one.

You might get better results asking that question in the Add-on Requests and Support forum. When you do, please describe what problems you're having in the game and what has changed since it last worked, especially new/updated mods. I've seen that error before, but it hasn't caused gameplay problems, so I can't help you without more information. Other mod users who frequent that forum might. If you could also upload the full output_log somewhere, it might also provide some context to whatever problems you're having.

So I have a problem with my mod.

I'm testing a mod that I'm updating to 0.24 (Quantum Struts), and I wanted to add KAS to the .cfg of the part itself. After I added it with this code:

MODULE
{
    name = KASModuleGrab
    evaPartPos = (0.0, 0.0, -0.15)
    evaPartDir = (0,0,-1)
    storable = true
    storedSize = 2
    attachOnPart = True
    attachOnEva = False
    attachOnStatic = False
}

It didn't work, so I deleted the lines again and made a separate MM config with this code:

@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[QuantumStrut]]
{
    MODULE
    {
        name = KASModuleGrab
        evaPartPos = (0.0, 0.0, -0.15)
        evaPartDir = (0,0,-1)
        storable = true
        storedSize = 2
        attachOnPart = True
        attachOnEva = False
        attachOnStatic = False
    }
}

This code worked yesterday perfectly on KSP. Today, I tested it again, but it didn't work anymore. I get this error in my Output_log:

Cannot find a Module of typename 'KASModuleGrab'

Can someone help me?

This code worked yesterday perfectly on KSP. Today, I tested it again, but it didn't work anymore. I get this error in my Output_log:

Cannot find a Module of typename 'KASModuleGrab'

Can someone help me?

Did you check the actual KAS dll and whether it got corrupted or misplaced? Because what the error message says is that it can't be found, not that your patch is somehow wrong.

The KAS.dll is in the Plugins folder of KAS itself, and the KASifyQSC.cfg (KAS addition) is in the folder of my mod.
